    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is total compensation higher for a PR or an EP holder in Singapore?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For the same gross salary, total compensation is higher for a PR because the employer contributes up to 17% of wages to CPF on top of the salary. The EP holder receives only the gross salary with no additional employer contributions."
